\{id:"D1",dlg:`M: Mary, would you join me for dinner tonight? W: You treated me last weekend. Now it's my turn. Shall we try something Italian?`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation?`,a:`The woman will treat the man to dinner.`\},\
\{id:"D2",dlg:`W: Good afternoon. I'm calling to inquire about the four-bedroom house you advertised in the newspaper. M: I'm sorry, but it's already sold.`,q:`What do we learn about the house from the conversation?`,a:`The house is already sold.`\},\
\{id:"D3",dlg:`W: John, what are you doing on your computer? Don't you remember your promise? M: This is not a game. It's only a crossword puzzle. They help increase my vocabulary.`,q:`What is the probable relationship between the speakers?`,a:`Mother and son.`\},\
\{id:"D4",dlg:`M: Do you still keep in touch with your parents regularly after all these years? W: Yes, of course. I call them at weekends when the rates are down 50%.`,q:`What do we learn about the woman from the conversation?`,a:`She calls her parents at weekends (when the rates are down 50%).`\},\
\{id:"D5",dlg:`M: Hurry, there's a bus coming. W: Why run? There will be another one in two or three minutes.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`There's no need to hurry because another bus is coming in two or three minutes.`\},\
\{id:"D6",dlg:`M: Wow, that's a big assignment we've got for the English class. W: Well, it's not as bad as it looks. It isn't due until Thursday morning.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`The assignment isn't due until Thursday morning.`\},\
\{id:"D7",dlg:`W: Hello, is that Steve? I'm stuck in a traffic jam. I'm afraid I can't make it before 7 o'clock. M: Never mind. I'll be here waiting for you.`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation?`,a:`The woman will be late and the man will be waiting for her.`\},\
\{id:"D8",dlg:`M: You really seem to enjoy your literature class. W: You are right. It has opened a new world for me. I'm exposed to the thoughts of some of the world's best writers. I've never read so much in my life.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`She really enjoys her literature class.`\},\
\{id:"D9",dlg:`W: I suppose you've bought some gifts for your family. M: Well, I've bought a shirt for my father and two books for my sister, but I haven't decided what to buy for my mother, probably some jewels.`,q:`Who did the man buy the books for?`,a:`His sister.`\},\
\{id:"D10",dlg:`W: Look! It says they want a junior sales manager, and it seems like it's a big company. M: Do they say anything about experience?`,q:`What are they talking about?`,a:`Job hunting / finding a job.`\},\
\{id:"D11",dlg:`W: I think we've covered everything. What about a cup of coffee before we move on to the next item? M: Good idea. I really can't wait another minute.`,q:`What does the woman suggest doing?`,a:`Having a cup of coffee.`\},\
\{id:"D12",dlg:`W: But what happens if it rains? What are we going to do then? M: We'll have to count on good weather, but if it does rain, the whole thing will have to be canceled.`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation?`,a:`If it rains, the whole thing will have to be canceled.`\},\
\{id:"D13",dlg:`W: You took an optional course this semester, didn't you? How is it going? M: Terrible. It seems like the more the professor talks, the less I understand.`,q:`How does the man feel about the course?`,a:`Terrible.`\},\
\{id:"D14",dlg:`W: Mark is playing computer games. M: Should he do that when the final exam is drawing near?`,q:`What does the man think Mark should do?`,a:`Review / Prepare for the exam.`\},\
\{id:"D15",dlg:`M: Jack seems to think that this year's basketball season will be disappointing. W: That's his opinion. Most others think differently.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`Most people think this year's basketball season will be interesting.`\},\
\{id:"D16",dlg:`M: Is this the check-in counter for flight 914 to Los Angeles? W: Yes, but I'm sorry the flight is delayed because of a minor mechanical problem.`,q:`What do we learn from this conversation?`,a:`The flight is delayed.`\},\
\{id:"D17",dlg:`M: Jessica, could you forward this email to all the club members? W: Sorry, the computer broke down this morning. I'll do it for you as soon as I have it fixed.`,q:`What does the woman imply?`,a:`She'll forward the email when the computer is fixed.`\},\
\{id:"D18",dlg:`W: Did you find the book for your reading assignment in the library? M: It closed before I got there; I had no idea it closes so early on weekends.`,q:`What does the man mean?`,a:`He didn't find the book because he had no idea the library closes so early on weekends.`\},\
\{id:"D19",dlg:`M: Did you check the power plug and press the play button? W: Yes. The power indicator was on and it was running. But somehow the sound didn't come through.`,q:`What was the woman probably trying to do?`,a:`She's probably playing music.`\},\
\{id:"D20",dlg:`M: Joanna, I'm awfully sorry. I didn't mean to hurt you. Shall we have a beer and forget the whole thing? W: OK, we can drop it this time, but don't do it again!`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation?`,a:`Joanna forgives the man.`\},\
\{id:"D21",dlg:`W: Airports are sad places. M: Sometimes, I guess. But we'll keep in touch and I'll fly over to see you at Christmas.`,q:`What are the speakers doing?`,a:`They are saying goodbye at the airport.`\},\
\{id:"D22",dlg:`M: Are you going to return to your present job after the vacation? W: No, I plan to graduate next semester. That means I will have to be a full-time student.`,q:`What will the woman do?`,a:`She will be a full-time student.`\},\
\{id:"D23",dlg:`W: John, are you doing research for Professor Williams this semester? M: Actually, I'm working as his teaching assistant.`,q:`What does the man mean?`,a:`He's working as Professor Williams' teaching assistant.`\},\
\{id:"D24",dlg:`M: I heard there are a few seats left for the show tonight. W: Really? I was under the impression that the tickets were sold out a long time ago.`,q:`What do we know from the woman's reply?`,a:`The tickets were sold out a long time ago.`\},\
\{id:"D25",dlg:`W: We have a complete range of famous brands here. How about this one? It's an Omega. M: I'm afraid that I'm not interested in watches with metal watchbands.`,q:`What do we know from the conversation?`,a:`The man is not interested in metal watchbands.`\},\
\{id:"D26",dlg:`W: What did you think of Tokyo? M: Thrilling, but not very attractive. All the buildings are gray and ugly. And it's very crowded.`,q:`What does the man think of Tokyo?`,a:`Thrilling but not very attractive. It's crowded.`\},\
\{id:"D27",dlg:`W: Drop me at the Manhattan Post Office please. M: Well, that's an hour's ride. Why not just post your mail here?`,q:`Who is the woman probably speaking to?`,a:`A taxi driver.`\},\
\{id:"D28",dlg:`M: Didn't I tell you over and over again that you wouldn't be able to climb the mountain unless you got enough sleep? W: You did, but I can't help it.`,q:`What do we know from the conversation?`,a:`They are going to climb the mountain but the woman didn't get enough sleep.`\},\
\{id:"D29",dlg:`W: This apartment has three bedrooms and a bath. Here's the kitchen. M: It seems a little small to me.`,q:`How many rooms are there in the apartment?`,a:`Five.`\},\
\{id:"D30",dlg:`M: This is a good seat. I'm glad you suggested the move. Here in the front section we can look out and enjoy the scenery. W: You feel the plane moving? Are we taking off now?`,q:`What can be inferred from the conversation?`,a:`They are on a plane and it's taking off.`\},\
\{id:"D31",dlg:`W: I want to go to the Chinese Visa Office in Central. It's by the Hong Kong Park. Here it's marked on this map. M: OK, I know where you mean.`,q:`Where does the conversation most probably take place?`,a:`On the street.`\},\
\{id:"D32",dlg:`W: The weather forecast said that we would have another wonderful day tomorrow. Shall we go and climb Mount Tai? M: Good idea. But we'd better leave very early, or else we'll get caught in the traffic.`,q:`What does the man suggest?`,a:`Leave early for Mount Tai (to avoid traffic).`\},\
\{id:"D33",dlg:`W: You never speak English unless you absolutely have to. I'll help you if you promise to speak nothing but English all the time. M: All right. Maybe I'll do that.`,q:`What can we learn from the conversation?`,a:`The man promises to speak nothing but English. The woman will help the man if he promises.`\},\
\{id:"D34",dlg:`M: Well, I will take the three-day tour of the island. W: Why not four days?`,q:`What does the woman suggest?`,a:`Take a four-day tour of the island.`\},\
\{id:"D35",dlg:`W: Can I make personal phone calls during office hours? M: Of course you can. But don't chat over the phone and don't let it hinder your work.`,q:`What does the man mean?`,a:`The woman can make personal calls during office hours as long as it doesn't hinder her work.`\},\
\{id:"D36",dlg:`M: How long does the journey take if I go by bus? W: It depends on the traffic. I think the Airport Express is your best bet.`,q:`What kind of place is the man probably going to?`,a:`The airport.`\},\
\{id:"D37",dlg:`M: Excuse me, madam, but did you see an old woman looking for her walking stick? W: An old woman, sir?`,q:`What's the man doing?`,a:`Looking for an old woman.`\},\
\{id:"D38",dlg:`W: Have you lived here long? M: I guess so. I first came here six years ago. Then one year after that I moved to Boston. But three years ago I was back here again.`,q:`How long has the man lived here all together?`,a:`Four years.`\},\
\{id:"D39",dlg:`M: Can I join you? I've never done such a thing before. W: You never pay attention to the people around you, not to mention showing concern about this society.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`She doesn't want the man to join her.`\},\
\{id:"D40",dlg:`W: When a book is on reserve, a student can go to the reserve room and ask the reserve librarian for the book. The student can have the book for a few hours, and must read it in the library. M: Thank you. I understand now.`,q:`What's the probable job of the woman?`,a:`A librarian.`\},\
\{id:"D41",dlg:`W: I heard you got full marks in the math exam. Congratulations! M: Thanks. I'm sure you also did a good job.`,q:`What's the probable relationship between the two speakers?`,a:`Classmates.`\},\
\{id:"D42",dlg:`W: Hi, Tony. How did your experiment go yesterday? M: Well, it wasn't as easy as I had thought. I have to continue doing it tonight.`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation?`,a:`The man has to continue doing the experiment tonight.`\},\
\{id:"D43",dlg:`M: I hear you are moving into a new apartment soon. W: Yes. But it is more expensive. My present neighbor plays the piano all night long.`,q:`Why is the woman moving?`,a:`Her neighbor plays the piano all night long.`\},\
\{id:"D44",dlg:`W: Mr. Jones, your student Bill shows great enthusiasm for musical instruments. M: I only wish he showed half as much for his English lessons.`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation about Bill?`,a:`He shows great enthusiasm for musical instruments but not much for English.`\},\
\{id:"D45",dlg:`W: Oh, dear! I'm starving. I can't walk any farther. M: Let's go to the restaurant across the street and get something to eat.`,q:`Where are the two people?`,a:`On the street.`\},\
\{id:"D46",dlg:`W: Why didn't you make an appointment to see the doctor last week when you first twisted your ankle? M: The injury didn't seem serious then.`,q:`Why didn't the man see the doctor earlier?`,a:`The injury didn't seem serious then.`\},\
\{id:"D47",dlg:`M: I wonder if Sue will be here by five o'clock. W: Her husband said she left home at half past four. She should be here at ten after five.`,q:`What time did Sue leave home?`,a:`Half past four.`\},\
\{id:"D48",dlg:`W: When will you be through with your work, John? M: Who knows? My boss usually finds something for me to do at the last minute.`,q:`What do we learn from the conversation?`,a:`John's boss usually finds something for him to do at the last minute.`\},\
\{id:"D49",dlg:`M: It's so hard for me to get to the morning class. But I'm going to fail if I keep skipping. I could hardly keep my eyes open before 10:00 a.m. W: Getting up early is a nightmare.`,q:`What can we know from the conversation?`,a:`They don't like to get up early. Getting up early is a nightmare.`\},\
\{id:"D50",dlg:`M: Hello, this is John Smith. Would you please get me through to Mr. Anderson? W: I'm sorry. He is having a meeting.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`Mr. Anderson is having a meeting so he can't talk to the man.`\},\
\{id:"D51",dlg:`W: Please do\\\\... Wait a moment. I don't feel like going out for breakfast. Can we call room service? M: Why not? What would you like for breakfast?`,q:`What will the man do?`,a:`Call room service for breakfast.`\},\
\{id:"D52",dlg:`W: Hello, I'd like a tourist guide, please. How much is that? M: It's free. There's a map inside.`,q:`Where is the conversation most probably taking place?`,a:`At the tourist service / tourist office.`\},\
\{id:"D53",dlg:`M: I have to finish four papers in a week, but I'd really have a hard time. W: I've told you it would be better if you prepared your papers at the beginning of the summer holiday.`,q:`What do we learn about the man?`,a:`He has to finish four papers in a week.`\},\
\{id:"D54",dlg:`M: Say, what time is it? Is it really only seven-fifteen? My watch says eight-fifteen. W: You forgot to set your watch back.`,q:`What time is it now?`,a:`Seven-fifteen.`\},\
\{id:"D55",dlg:`M: Hi, I'm interested in renting a two-bedroom apartment. W: Okay. If you have a seat, one of our rental agents will be with you in a moment.`,q:`What does the woman mean?`,a:`A rental agent will come in a moment.`\},\
\{id:"D56",dlg:`M: I'm going on holiday, and I need some foreign currency. W: Cash or traveler's checks?`,q:`What is the probable relationship between the two speakers?`,a:`A bank clerk and a customer.`\},\
\{id:"D57",dlg:`W: I have to call Kate and tell her about the interview tomorrow afternoon. M: Why bother? You will see her this afternoon at the meeting.`,q:`What does the man mean?`,a:`The woman doesn't have to call Kate.`\},\
\{id:"D58",dlg:`W: There'll be a meeting for the handicapped the week after next. They decided that every participant should wear a uniform. M: Yeah. I'm the right man up to the designing job.`,q:`What is the man going to do?`,a:`Design a uniform for the handicapped.`\},\
\{id:"D59",dlg:`W: First, what price range were you interested in? M: Somewhere between \\\\$400 and \\\\$450 a month.`,q:`How much will the man probably have to pay a year?`,a:`\\\\$4,800 to \\\\$5,400 dollars.`\},\
