const QI=[\
\{id:"I1",title:"Computers",\
 passage:"The first computers were very large \'97 some were as big as several rooms. Over time, the technology improved and computers became smaller. Now, personal computers are everywhere. They are supposed to improve the quality of our lives, but they have not made life better.\\n\\nComputers waste a lot of time. Computers are machines, and machines often break. There are many stories about people who have wasted time because of computer problems.\\n\\nComputers also hurt relationships between people. People often sit in front of their computers instead of being with their family and friends. This can damage relationships between people.",\
 summary:"The author believes that computers do not make our lives better. First, they waste a lot of time when they break. Second, they hurt relationships because people spend less time with family. Therefore, computers can damage our social lives.",\
 opinion:"I completely agree with the author's opinion for several important reasons.\\n\\nFirst of all, using computers less can provide many benefits to the community. It helps to solve many existing problems. For example, it can save a lot of time and resources for many families.\\n\\nSecondly, when people focus on face-to-face communication, they become more responsible and gain more valuable experience.\\n\\nIn conclusion, I believe we should support the author's idea to create a brighter future for everyone."\},\
\{id:"I2",title:"Teenagers and Work",\
 passage:"Schools teach students a lot, but having a job can help students in ways that schools cannot. All teenagers should work while they are in school.\\n\\nTeenagers who have jobs can learn about different job fields. Such experiences make it easier for students to decide what kind of job they should look for when they graduate.\\n\\nStudents who work also learn how to manage their own money. By working hard for their own money, teenagers learn its value. A part-time job provides students with experiences and skills that cannot be taught in school.",\
 summary:"The author believes that all teenagers should work while they are in school. First, jobs help students learn about different careers. Second, working teaches teenagers how to manage money. Therefore, part-time jobs provide useful life skills.",\
 opinion:"I completely agree with the author's opinion.\\n\\nFirst of all, working helps students learn real-world skills that schools cannot teach. It helps them make better decisions about their future careers.\\n\\nSecondly, teenagers who work learn the value of money through personal experience. This teaches them to be responsible and self-sufficient.\\n\\nIn conclusion, part-time jobs are an important way for teenagers to prepare for the real world."\},\
\{id:"I3",title:"Zoos",\
 passage:"Over the past several years, the number of people visiting zoos has reached record levels. Zoos attract a lot of tourists and families. But they are not the best place for animals to live.\\n\\nA zoo can provide only limited space for each animal. Many zoos keep big cats in very small spaces. Having too little space can be bad for the animals' minds and bodies.\\n\\nIt is also important to understand that zoos can be harmful and even deadly for some animals. Animals from different regions live very close together. They can get sick because they are not used to each other.",\
 summary:"The author believes that zoos are not the best place for animals. First, zoos provide very limited space. Second, animals can get sick or hurt. Therefore, we should choose other family activities.",\
 opinion:"I completely agree with the author's opinion.\\n\\nFirst of all, animals in zoos are deprived of the space they need to stay healthy. Animals like bears and big cats need to roam large territories.\\n\\nSecondly, keeping animals from different regions together can lead to the spread of disease.\\n\\nIn conclusion, we should find better ways to appreciate wildlife, such as nature documentaries or responsible wildlife sanctuaries."\},\
\{id:"I4",title:"Big City vs Countryside",\
 passage:"Although the countryside can be more peaceful than a big city, it is better for children to grow up in a big city.\\n\\nChildren who grow up in a big city have more opportunities. If a child wants to sing, dance, or play a musical instrument, he or she can easily find different teachers or clubs. In addition, most big cities have excellent museums, zoos, art galleries, and libraries.\\n\\nChildren can also develop a world view in a big city. In big cities, there are people from many different backgrounds. It is good for young people to meet people from different cultures.",\
 summary:"The author believes it is better for children to grow up in a big city. First, cities offer more opportunities for learning. Second, children can meet different people and develop a world view. Therefore, city life better prepares children for the real world.",\
 opinion:"I completely agree with the author's opinion.\\n\\nFirst of all, big cities provide access to a wide range of educational resources and cultural experiences that are simply not available in rural areas.\\n\\nSecondly, exposure to diverse cultures helps children develop empathy and open-mindedness from an early age.\\n\\nIn conclusion, despite the peacefulness of the countryside, a big city environment is more beneficial for children's overall development."\},\
\{id:"I5",title:"Public Transportation",\
 passage:"Few cities have enough money to pay for all the things they wish to do. Cities should spend more money on improving public transportation than on improving roads for private cars.\\n\\nMany cities are growing more and more each year. The population is rising, which creates congestion. Cities should focus on building public transportation so that congestion is reduced.\\n\\nReducing the number of drivers on the road can also help reduce air pollution. Cars are one of the biggest sources of air pollution, contributing to global climate change.",\
 summary:"The author believes that cities should spend more money on public transportation. First, it can reduce traffic congestion. Second, it helps reduce air pollution. Therefore, developing buses and trains is very important.",\
 opinion:"I completely agree with the author's opinion.\\n\\nFirst of all, public transportation reduces traffic congestion and allows cities to use land more efficiently for parks and housing.\\n\\nSecondly, fewer cars on the road means significantly less air pollution, which benefits residents' health and helps address climate change.\\n\\nIn conclusion, every city should prioritize the development of efficient, affordable public transportation systems."\}\
];\
